    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/825</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 10, 12.20
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1611. Press reports:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Journal de Genève</hi>, 9th, gives substance Hungarian press
                    comments, President <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName>’s note.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Az Est</hi>, Budapest, finds note so clear, worthy support all
                    genuine friends peace and patriots. America thus expresses itself unreservedly
                    for peace without annexation, and this the essential for Hungary.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Magyarország</hi>, organ <persName corresp="#p_KCM1"
                        >Károlyi</persName> party, states <persName corresp="#p_WW1"
                        >Wilson</persName> has won with courageous reply, recognition all sincere
                    friends peace. Those condemning note display war-devil spirit and do not desire
                    peace. Whoever opposes <persName corresp="#p_WW1">Wilson</persName> declares
                    himself enemy of Hungarian nation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
